Police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said the store was robbed around 09:35, when the men broke into premises and fired a shot. “They took two bags of jewellery. The police officers responded and there was a shootout. The suspects fled the scene in their getaway vehicle which was later found abandoned in the Inanda area.” A case of robbery had been opened for investigation at Phoenix SAPS. Reaction Unit SA head Prem Balram said the men fled in a black Mercedes-Benz which was later recovered in the Bambhayi informal settlement by police. “Reaction officers and police are currently searching for the heavily armed suspects.” News24 Please note you must be a Maverick Insider to comment. Sign up here or sign in if you are already an Insider.